data.description: Welcome to a slice of The American Dream at 19739 185th Street, Marshall, MO! This charming property sits on a sprawling 9.6-acre lot, offering the perfect blend of tranquility and opportunity. Nestled amidst the serene countryside, this home is a haven for nature enthusiasts, hobbyists, and those seeking a peaceful retreat.As you approach, you'll fall in love by the picturesque surroundings, with lush greenery and mature trees framing the front and back of the property. The inviting 3-bedroom, 1 and a 1/2-bathroom residence exudes country modern charm and warmth. Step inside to discover a spacious living area adorned leading to an open-concept kitchen and dining area boasting ample cabinetry, granite countertops, and modern appliances.The primary loft is a serene sanctuary with an ensuite bathroom, ensuring your privacy and comfort. Two additional bedrooms provide flexibility for guests, a home office, or a hobby room. Natural light streams through large windows, creating a bright and inviting atmosphere throughout the home.One of the standout features of this property is the impressive 40x56 detached shop, perfect for woodworking, automotive projects, or storing your outdoor equipment. With its generous size and versatility, the possibilities are endless. You'd never know it from the front, but hidden amidst the trees on the North of the lot is a developed and stocked pond with a small dock!This property is conveniently located, providing easy access to Marshall's amenities but still within Sweet Springs school district. Whether you're yearning for a peaceful rural lifestyle, a place to pursue your hobbies, or a combination of both, this 19739 185th Street residence offers it all. Don't miss your chance to make this slice of country paradise your own. Schedule a showing today to experience the tranquility and endless possibilities of this remarkable property! 2024-01-12
